salvaje is a fringe-limbed member of the genus, and the only other member sampled is the phylogenetically basal E. miotympanum (some place it in another Genus, Rheohyla). We use minera as a fringe-limbed standin to represent that likely monophyletic clade. See Mendelson III, J. R., Eichenbaum, A., & Campbell, J. A. (2015). Taxonomic review of the populations of the fringe-limbed treefrogs (Hylidae: Ecnomiohyla) in Mexico and nuclear Central America. South american journal of herpetology, 10(3), 187-194.
